message: The name, börek, comes from the Persian burak (بورک), the diminutive form of būra or buġra (بوره/بغره), meaning "Persian stew",[3] and refers to any dish made with yufka (filo).  The Persian word Bureh goes back to the Middle Persian *Bōrak. This word ultimately goes back to the Proto-Indo-European root *bher- which meant "to carve, cut, split,".[4] Turkic languages have borrowed this word from Persian.[1] The name of another pastry, Shekarbura is also borrowed from the same Persian word.[5]
